explanation: Bitmask DP enumerates all 2^(2n) subsets, storing the best score for each subset. For each even-sized subset, it tries every pair of remaining indices, computes gcd, and updates the DP table. The small n (≤7) keeps the state space manageable (2^14 = 16384 states).

